Confidence interval with stats known.

Confidence interval with stats known.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Default Description
avg Nums Sample average/mean or population (array of numbers)
c number <optional>
 .95 Confidence (eg.: 95%)
n number <optional>
 Number of data
sd number <optional>
 Standard Deviation
Since:
  • 1.0
Source:
  • maths.js, line 3296
To Do:
  • Make sd optional after having a t-Distribution table calculator
Returns:
Confidence interval
Type
Array.<number>
Example
//If the first paraMetre is a number (hence the sample mean), than the rest of the paraMetres are necessary
var ci = confidenceInterval(6.34, .75, 5, .74);
//Otherwise if the first paraMetre is an array (of numbers), than the rest of the paraMetres are useless (except the second one)
ci = confidenceInterval([5.7, 6.63, 6.57, 7.7, 7.51], .75);
